product_name: e.l.f. CosmeticsHalo Glow Powder Filter Pressed Powder
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty Freee.l.f. Cosmetics' Halo Glow Powder Filter is an ultra-fine setting powder that helps blur the appearance of pores and reduce the look of shine for a naturally soft-focus vibe. The light-as-air pressed powder formula delivers light, buildable coverage (no caking, and it' crease-resistant!).

reviews.headline: Best
reviews.comments: This powder gives my skin a soft, luminous finish without being cakey. It sets makeup beautifully while adding a subtle glow. I love using it over foundation for a filtered, radiant look. Perfect for those who want a healthy-looking complexion with staying power. [I received this product in exchange for my honest review]

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: This is the best pressed powder I've ever tried. It comes with a powder puff and a space to keep said puff, so I don't have to worry about having one with me. It keeps my makeup on all day, and the finish is so natural. Best part is the shade actually matches my skin tone. Definitely worth it!

reviews.headline: Love love love!!
reviews.comments:
I received this product in exchange for my honest review
This pressed powder is super lightweight and gives my skin a smooth, natural glow without looking cakey. It blurs pores just enough and sets my makeup nicely without making me look too matte. Great for everyday wear I'll definitely keep this in my routine!

reviews.headline: The perfect powder!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I wear very little makeup and this is the perfect amount of coverage for me. It goes on the skin very easily and does not cake. I like the compact because it has a nice mirror and a separate compartment for the puff that comes with it. The scent is very minimal which is great for my sensitive skin.

reviews.headline: Yes!! Must get
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love this pressed powder. A little goes a long way! It provides an extra layer of coverage, smooths out my skin and brightens it! It comes with a thin puff as well! Easy to use and great glowy effect.

reviews.headline: Love this
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was really excited to try it since I've read really good things about it, but unfortunately it's too dark a shade for my skin to use all over my face. However, I have used it to seal the contour of my face and it has been effective, although sometimes it has a very sandy tone, so I try to use it mostly at night.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Unfortunately, I merely liked it. (Sorry, e.l.f.!)

I received a generous, free, retail-sized compact of Halo Glow Pressed Powder (shade: Light Neutral) from TopBox Circle a few weeks ago, and having tried the product several times, I have determined that the product itself is GOOD. However, at the moment, with seasonal and hormonal changes (perimenopause) as well as recent changes in prescription medications (affecting my skin's texture and hydration), e.l.f.'s Halo Setting Powder is something that I'll have to continue using for the next couple of months, when my skin has better adjusted to current changes.

At 50, with maturing (but typically combination, clear) skin, I LOVE that there's no talc in the formulation! The fine-milled texture is very soft, and the Light Neutral shade was perfect for my skin tone! Due to the currently dehydrated, slightly drier skin, unfortunately, the Halo Glow Pressed Powder will likely have to be used only to set and touch up areas of my T-zone, as the MATTE finish accentuates the currently dehydrated, slightly drier state of my perimenopausal skin. I might also try buffing the powder in with a kabuki brush, for a possibly more diffused, airbrushed look, but suspect the powder will be strictly for SETTING and touching up my t-zone until such time as my skin (hopefully) returns to its typically more balanced and hydrated state. 

In a world full of too many talc-filled powders, the e.l.f. Halo Glow Powder Filter IS a good bargain, and I appreciated the opportunity to try it for free!
faceoff_positive.headline: I Wanted to LOVE It, But...

faceoff_negative.comments: I got this product for free in exchange of my honest opinion.  I got  e.l.f. Cosmetics HaloGlow Powder Filter in Deep Neutral good option for those looking for a soft luminous finish it has finely texture that applies smoothly on the skin leaving the skin glowing, it helps blurring imperfections, it doesn't provide coverage best to use as a setting powder.
